Nigerian pop star, Davido has broken silence following the ongoing attack on Nigerians in South Africa. In his reaction, he noted that if Nigeria was a good country, there wouldn’t be any reason for Nigerians to reside in South Africa. Davido on his recent tweet expresses heartbreak over the xenophobic attack, questioned the wellbeing of Nigerians and he has been supported by thousands of people. The “Blow my mind” crooner who just had his marriage introduction with his fiancee yesterday posted on Twitter: “If our country good ? Wetin we go find go southy ???” See his post below; Source